School meals are the only source of nutrition for millions of children, but in emergencies, education is seen as a luxury.

@WFP is working to help kids stay educated &amp; fed especially in crisis affected regions.

Thursday is International School Meals Day: https://t.co/SWnUQlI4Im https://t.co/doPQEYdALx

The war in Ukraine is already impacting millions of lives inside and outside the country.

@WFP warns that as the crisis worsens, many countries will face soaring food prices, catastrophic hunger and growing instability. https://t.co/cbtdsjWe1m

 https://t.co/H53UsQ4NUA

Afghanistan: 23 million people are facing acute food insecurity. 

Years of drought compounded by on-going conflict and economic instability have lead to a dire humanitarian crisis.

@WFP is working to support families in need. https://t.co/3bKlecYRkK https://t.co/3EkjwCdoQN

The ongoing crisis in Ukraine is disrupting &amp; overwhelming health services.

@WHO is working to help people in need, including refugees in neighbouring countries.

You can support their efforts: https://t.co/LbPz34hOl1
